&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An opportunity has arisen for qualified Psychological Wellbeing Practitioner’s (PWP) to join City Health Care Partnership’s Lets talk IAPT service. You will be providing evidence based step 2 CBT based assessment and treatment intervention  to a diverse range of clients from a variety of backgrounds and whose first language may not be English. As a qualified PWP you will have knowledge and experience of working with people experiencing mild to moderate mental health issues.  It is therefore essential that you are able to communicate sensitively and effectively are non-judgemental and compassionate. The successful candidates will be proactive in their own development and will engage in peer and individual practice supervision and review. You will be able to work flexibly across the area of service delivery and will be proactive in organisational, service and personal development. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; For further information please refer to Job description and Person specification. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Other enquiries can be made to Kate Cowl - kate.cowl@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
